<dl id="n01083g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01083g">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01083g"> 83(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tan (tent) ~ <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n01083g"> <li>FW isotext </li><li><ms href="#n01083g">MS BL 47471b-77v</ms> </li><li>JJA 48:010 <a name="h1B0d" href="../../ff/fdra/hda.htm#h1B0d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/h/h1b0d.htm#n01083g">Draft: I.8&sect;1B.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[GIPSIES IN WINTER.]</font> It is part of his racial pride that makes the Romanichal reluctant to abandon the tawny tent in winter for a house. I have heard an old gipsy say that when lying convalescent in a hospital he &ldquo;was terribly afeared that the ceiling might come down on him.&rdquo; He was glad to get back to &ldquo;the old <mark><i>tan</i>&rdquo; (tent)</mark> and put <i>kosht</i> (wood) on the <i>yog</i> (fire) and &ldquo;feel comfortable-like again.&rdquo; <small> <a name="DM28dec22" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DM28dec22"><cite title="source">Daily Mail</cite></a> (28 December 1922) 6/5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
